Introduction

Rocket Punch (also known as RCPC) is a girl group under Woollim Entertainment. They made their debut on August 7, 2019, with their first mini album "Pink Punch" and the lead track "BIM BAM BUM."

The group's name and logo were revealed on July 22, 2019, through a logo motion video and the launch of their official social media accounts. A concept film introducing the six members was released the following day. Individual teaser photos for "Pink Punch" were unveiled on August 1, leading up to their official debut.

Rocket Punch also made their debut in Japan with the album "Bubble Up!" on August 4, 2021.

On May 23, 2024, Woollim Entertainment announced the departure of Juri from Rocket Punch and the agency. Later, on December 27, 2024, the company revealed that the exclusive contracts of Yeonhee, Yunkyoung, Sohee, and Dahyun would end on December 31, 2024.
